The following comment does not apply only to A02.1 but to all items that use "cup" in their serving example. I cannot remember the list of countries from the top of my head, but the "cup" measure will have a standardized meaning and people will know what you are referring to only in the US. Outside of the US, if you say cup, it may be understood differently by respondents within and between countries. I don't know if there will be an opportunity with the screener to show an actual US cup but that might help.
